- Yeah.

30
00:02:26,777 --> 00:02:29,644
<i>[ Sniffing, Grunting ]</i>

31
00:02:30,881 --> 00:02:33,315
- [ Screaming ]
- Shoo, nerds! Shoo!

32
00:02:33,417 --> 00:02:34,611
[ Muttering ]

33
00:02:37,121 --> 00:02:39,351
Well, this muscle shirt's
a pretty good find.

34
00:02:39,456 --> 00:02:41,356
Dad, that's a sports bra.

35
00:02:41,458 --> 00:02:44,325
All I know is I'm finally
getting the support I need.

36
00:02:44,428 --> 00:02:46,453
Look, Dad!
Barber hair!

37
00:02:46,563 --> 00:02:48,895
[ Sniffing ]
Ooh, Italian.

38
00:02:50,100 --> 00:02:53,228
[ Chuckles ]
Hey, Vinnie. How's about a pizza?

39
00:02:53,337 --> 00:02:55,498
I got-a no job.
[ Chuckles ]

40
00:02:55,606 --> 00:02:59,440
<i>[ Gasps ] Mamma mia!
Look what the Hawaiian restaurant threw out.</i>

41
00:02:59,543 --> 00:03:02,512
<i>Get out of my dreams
and into my car.</i>

42
00:03:02,613 --> 00:03:04,638
<i>[ High-pitched Humming ]</i>

43
00:03:04,748 --> 00:03:09,117
<i>- [ Humming Continues ]
- I don't remember the air in the kitchen
being so wavy.</i>

44
00:03:09,219 --> 00:03:12,188
<i>[ Sniffs ]
Good lord! That's gas!</i>

45
00:03:12,289 --> 00:03:15,349
<i>[ Groans ]
Hmm.</i>

46
00:03:15,459 --> 00:03:17,825
- Hmm?
- [ Homer's Voice ] Behold!

47
00:03:17,928 --> 00:03:19,953
I am King Talkie Tiki!

48
00:03:20,064 --> 00:03:21,964
[ Screaming ]

49
00:03:22,066 --> 00:03:24,660
Hey, Flanders.
Can your god do that?

50
00:03:24,768 --> 00:03:28,169
A-Actually, Homer, you and I
worship the same god, so-

51
00:03:28,272 --> 00:03:32,009
Irregardless!
I am your god now.

52
00:03:33,914 --> 00:03:36,314
Homer you can just re-wrap the gas line

53
00:03:36,715 --> 00:03:40,708
- Do you know how dangerous that is?
- Do not anger Talkie Tiki!

54
00:03:40,818 --> 00:03:42,877
I am all power-

55
00:03:42,986 --> 00:03:45,511
[ Screams ] I'll be at Moe's.
[ Whimpering ]

56
00:03:47,091 --> 00:03:48,991
So I says to the cop, ''No...

57
00:03:49,093 --> 00:03:52,460
<i>you're driving under the influence
of bein' a jerk!''</i>

58
00:03:52,563 --> 00:03:55,327
[ Laughing ]

59
00:03:55,432 --> 00:03:58,765
- [ Sighs ]
- Hey, Barney, what's with the glum face?

60
00:03:58,869 --> 00:04:01,133
You glum or somethin'?
Huh, glummy?

61
00:04:01,238 --> 00:04:05,368
You know, it was my birthday last week
and no one remembered.

62
00:04:05,476 --> 00:04:08,343
- What are you, nuts?
- I threw you a party at my house.

63
00:04:08,445 --> 00:04:11,812
You lie! Why would I
not remember my own-

64
00:04:11,915 --> 00:04:14,713
<i>[ Gulps, Sighs ]
birthday?</i>

65
00:04:14,818 --> 00:04:19,118
But we did have a shindig for you, Barn.
We even videotaped it. Look.

66
00:04:23,193 --> 00:04:26,185
[ Moe ]
Oh, that's it, baby. All for Moe.

67
00:04:26,296 --> 00:04:29,629
Oh, yeah, work the slot.
Show me the package.

68
00:04:29,733 --> 00:04:32,827
Whoa. [ Laughs ]
That's-That's a project I'm workin' on. Sorry.

69
00:04:34,238 --> 00:04:36,138
[ Bart ]
Okay, Mom. We're rollin'.

70
00:04:36,240 --> 00:04:39,573
I wrote a poem for Barney
on this special occasion.

71
00:04:39,676 --> 00:04:43,442
''Now that you're one year older,
the time flew by so fast''-

72
00:04:43,547 --> 00:04:45,014
- Bart.
- [ Bart Laughing ]

73
00:04:45,115 --> 00:04:47,015
<i>Give me that.
[ Groans ]</i>

74
00:04:47,117 --> 00:04:50,450
I'm just sayin' that when we die...

75
00:04:50,554 --> 00:04:54,581
there's gonna be a planet for the French,
a planet for the Chinese...

76
00:04:54,691 --> 00:04:56,750
and we'll all be a lot happier.

77
00:04:56,860 --> 00:04:59,590
<i>- Mr. Gumble, you're upsetting me.
- No, I'm not.</i>

78
00:04:59,696 --> 00:05:03,723
<i>Gee. Is that what
I look like when I'm drunk?</i>

79
00:05:03,834 --> 00:05:08,032
You wish. That's the stage
we call ''Professor Barney.''

80
00:05:08,138 --> 00:05:12,370
<i>Talkative, coherent, even insightful.
Here's drunk.</i>

81
00:05:12,476 --> 00:05:14,376
[ Stairs Squeaking ]

82
00:05:14,478 --> 00:05:18,915
[ High-pitched Voice ]
Well, I'm off to market. [ Burps ]

83
00:05:19,016 --> 00:05:21,507
Marge, you're making
a complete fool of yours-

84
00:05:21,618 --> 00:05:23,518
Oh, it's just Barney.

85
00:05:23,620 --> 00:05:26,316
[ Shouts ]

86
00:05:26,423 --> 00:05:30,723
<i>[ Gasps ]
Precious alcohol, soaking in the shag!</i>

87
00:05:30,827 --> 00:05:33,261
<i>[ Gulping ]</i>

88
00:05:33,363 --> 00:05:36,093
<i>- [ Growling ]
- [ Whining ]</i>

89
00:05:36,200 --> 00:05:39,135
Oh. How embarrassing.

90
00:05:39,236 --> 00:05:42,399
- Well, how did this happen?
- Oh, that. You've had that for a while.

91
00:05:42,506 --> 00:05:45,771
Yeah, I can't really
picture you without it.

92
00:05:45,876 --> 00:05:48,037
Oh, I'm a disgrace!

93
00:05:48,145 --> 00:05:50,238
Disgracefully hilarious.

94
00:05:50,347 --> 00:05:53,339
You passed out before we could
even give you your presents.

95
00:05:53,450 --> 00:05:56,681
I still got mine. Barney, I got you
what no drunk can do without-

96
00:05:56,787 --> 00:05:59,255
<i>morning-after stationery.</i>

97
00:05:59,356 --> 00:06:03,258
- [ Laughing ]
- And I got you helicopter-flyin' lessons.

98
00:06:03,360 --> 00:06:06,454
Can you imagine this booze-bag
at the wheel of a whirlybird?

99
00:06:06,563 --> 00:06:08,656
[ Laughs ]
He'd be all, ''Look at me!

100
00:06:08,765 --> 00:06:11,063
I'm a tanked-up loser
in a helicopter!''

101
00:06:11,168 --> 00:06:13,636
[ Laughing ]

102
00:06:13,737 --> 00:06:17,173
Ah, anyway, happy b-day, pumpkin.

103
00:06:18,242 --> 00:06:21,405
So, I'm a tanked-up loser?

104
00:06:21,511 --> 00:06:23,445
Is that how you see me?

105
00:06:23,547 --> 00:06:28,041
Oh, sounds like a certain loser
could use some tankin' up.

106
00:06:29,453 --> 00:06:31,717
<i>- [ Grunts ]
- Hey, hey. Where you goin'?</i>

107
00:06:31,822 --> 00:06:35,383
I'll show you.
I'm gonna take these helicopter lessons.

108
00:06:35,492 --> 00:06:39,952
Wait a minute, Barney. You gotta be sober to fly.
I mean, it's not like driving a car.

109
00:06:40,063 --> 00:06:43,794
- Then I'm gonna quit drinkin'!
- [ Laughing ]

110
00:06:43,900 --> 00:06:46,425
- No, I mean it.
- [ Laughing Continues ]

111
00:06:46,536 --> 00:06:49,471
You won't see me here again, ever!

112
00:06:53,744 --> 00:06:55,678
Wait. That ain't funny.
He's my best customer.

113
00:06:55,779 --> 00:06:58,043
Well, the handwriting's on the wall.

114
00:06:58,148 --> 00:07:00,742
To stay afloat, this bar
is gonna have to go queer.

115
00:07:00,851 --> 00:07:02,842
You mean it's not? Oh.
[ Clicks Tongue ]

116
00:07:02,953 --> 00:07:05,649
<i>Wrong again,
Gay Guide to Springfield.</i>

117
00:07:11,194 --> 00:07:13,788
Farewell, my longneck friends.

118
00:07:13,897 --> 00:07:15,489
<i>[ Grunts ]</i>

119
00:07:18,135 --> 00:07:20,103
[ Shatters ]

120
00:07:21,338 --> 00:07:23,238
All right, world.

121
00:07:23,340 --> 00:07:26,901
<i>Get ready to meet
the clean and sober Barney Gumble.</i>

122
00:07:28,578 --> 00:07:31,240
<i>Whee! Give me a beer.</i>

123
00:07:31,348 --> 00:07:33,339
I knew you'd be back.

124
00:07:33,450 --> 00:07:35,543
Santeria, you're the greatest.

125
00:07:36,853 --> 00:07:39,253
Barney, didn't you say you
were going to stop drinking?

126
00:07:39,356 --> 00:07:43,884
I know, but it's so hard!
Please help me, Homer.

127
00:07:43,994 --> 00:07:48,363
You came to the right guy. I'll straighten you out...
right after I finish this beer.

128
00:07:48,465 --> 00:07:50,933
<i>- Mmm. [ Gulping ]
- Ohh.</i>

129
00:07:51,034 --> 00:07:53,901
- Mmm.
- Ohh.

130
00:07:54,004 --> 00:07:57,531
[ Mumbling ]
Oh, man, that's sweet.

131
00:07:57,641 --> 00:07:59,575
Okay, let's go.

132
00:07:59,676 --> 00:08:04,409
My name is Barney,
and I'm an alcoholic.

133
00:08:04,514 --> 00:08:07,972
I feel for you, pally, but, uh, you want A.A.
This is Triple ''A.''

134
00:08:08,085 --> 00:08:10,952
Oh. My name is Homer,
and I'm planning a trip to Saint Louis.

135
00:08:11,054 --> 00:08:14,080
- East Saint Louis?
- Is there any other Saint Louis?

136
00:08:15,625 --> 00:08:19,152
<i>[ Chattering ]</i>

137
00:08:20,197 --> 00:08:22,290
Uh, welcome back, Homer.

138
00:08:22,399 --> 00:08:24,993
I see you finally hit rock bottom.

139
00:08:25,102 --> 00:08:28,299
<i>[ Raspberries ]
Not a chance. I can sink way lower.</i>

140
00:08:28,405 --> 00:08:30,430
I just came to help
my friend Barney.

141
00:08:30,540 --> 00:08:32,565
We all know why
we're here, don't we?

142
00:08:32,676 --> 00:08:36,476
To keep ourselves sober, and to network.
So let's get started.

143
00:08:36,580 --> 00:08:39,310
Well, after I lost
my third job in two days...

144
00:08:39,416 --> 00:08:41,680
<i>old Gil was in a pit of despair.</i>

145
00:08:41,785 --> 00:08:44,310
And that's when you realized
you were an alcoholic?

146
00:08:44,421 --> 00:08:48,881
Oh, no, I never touch the stuff. But you don't
have to be drunk to know the value of Amway.

147
00:08:48,992 --> 00:08:51,893
<i>- [ Gasping ]
- Now, this is used crankcase oil...</i>

148
00:08:51,995 --> 00:08:54,520
<i>which you ladies know
is murder to clean up,you know?</i>

149
00:08:54,631 --> 00:08:56,531
And company's coming-

150
00:08:56,633 --> 00:09:01,002
Oh! You're doing this at the worst possible time.
Oh, your finger's in my eye!

151
00:09:02,839 --> 00:09:05,865
I have a problem with alcohol
and I need help.

152
00:09:05,976 --> 00:09:08,206
Well, your recovery begins today.

153
00:09:08,311 --> 00:09:12,179
And we promise you all the sugar cookies
and secondhand smoke you can handle.

154
00:09:12,282 --> 00:09:14,580
These sugar cookies you speak of...

155
00:09:14,684 --> 00:09:16,652
are they real or symbolic?

156
00:09:16,753 --> 00:09:19,221
They're on that table over there.

157
00:09:19,322 --> 00:09:21,347
Oh, I don't wanna walk that far.

158
00:09:21,458 --> 00:09:25,588
Anything that takes 1 2 steps
isn't worth doin'.

159
00:09:25,695 --> 00:09:28,892
<i>Get it? Huh? Twelve?
[ Laughs ]</i>

160
00:09:28,999 --> 00:09:31,058
<i>Steps?
[ Giggles ]</i>

161
00:09:31,168 --> 00:09:33,762
Hey, how did I get out here?

162
00:09:33,870 --> 00:09:38,034
<i>- ## [ Instrumental ]
- [ Giggles ] Hurt everyone.</i>

163
00:09:38,141 --> 00:09:41,668
<i>- Did Ga Ga just say ''Hurt everyone''?
- [ Laughs ] Ga Ga- Cute name.</i>

164
00:09:41,778 --> 00:09:46,374
- [ Man ] The Springfield
phone book needs a new cover.
- [ Together] It does?

165
00:09:46,483 --> 00:09:50,852
Send us your snapshots, and if we select yours,
you win a fabulous mystery prize.

166
00:09:50,954 --> 00:09:53,115
To enter, send your film
to this address.

167
00:09:53,223 --> 00:09:55,123
Too quick? Try again.

168
00:09:55,225 --> 00:09:57,125
Did you get it?
Here it is.

169
00:09:57,227 --> 00:09:59,957
Coming in from the left.
Don't delay. Do it today!

170
00:10:00,063 --> 00:10:03,726
- You think we should enter?
- Well, it shouldn't be too hard
to beat the old photo.

171
00:10:03,834 --> 00:10:04,926
<i>[ Bart ]
Ugh.</i>

172
00:10:07,304 --> 00:10:09,864
<i>- Hmm.
- It's gotta be here somewhere.</i>

173
00:10:09,973 --> 00:10:12,100
Hmm. Hmm. Hmm.

174
00:10:12,209 --> 00:10:14,370
Hey, here's a camera.

175
00:10:15,779 --> 00:10:18,043
And it's still got
a roll of film in it.

176
00:10:18,148 --> 00:10:21,606
Man, these old cameras
are really built solid.

177
00:10:21,718 --> 00:10:25,085
- Bart, we need that to win the contest.
- Win the what now?

178
00:10:26,923 --> 00:10:29,517
[ No Audible Dialogue ]

179
00:10:29,626 --> 00:10:32,925
[ Inhales, Exhales ]
Here goes.

180
00:10:33,029 --> 00:10:37,830
So he's so busy worrying about the front rotor,
he walks right into the back one.

181
00:10:38,935 --> 00:10:40,835
Only in this business.

182
00:10:40,937 --> 00:10:43,770
I'd like to sign up
for helicopter lessons.

183
00:10:43,874 --> 00:10:48,072
Sorry, pal, but it takes a special kind of man
to pilot these birds.

184
00:10:48,178 --> 00:10:50,112
- I got a coupon.
- Okay, get in.

185
00:10:53,183 --> 00:10:56,710
Elvis played a chopper pilot one time.
[ Chuckles ]

186
00:10:56,820 --> 00:10:59,380
He made so many darn mistakes...

187
00:10:59,489 --> 00:11:01,389
we were just laughin' at him.

188
00:11:01,491 --> 00:11:03,755
<i>- Great singer though.
- Oh, absolutely.</i>

189
00:11:03,860 --> 00:11:07,387
You know who else I like
is that, uh, Leo Sayer.

190
00:11:07,497 --> 00:11:09,556
Anyway, we're nice and level now.

191
00:11:09,666 --> 00:11:11,691
How would you like
to take the controls?

192
00:11:11,801 --> 00:11:14,497
- You think I'm ready?
- Sure, I do.

193
00:11:14,604 --> 00:11:17,368
One sec. Testing, black box.
One, two.

194
00:11:17,474 --> 00:11:20,204
[ Screaming ]

195
00:11:20,310 --> 00:11:22,210
She's all yours, friend.

196
00:11:22,312 --> 00:11:24,678
<i>[ Grunting ]</i>

197
00:11:24,781 --> 00:11:27,443
Whoa. Whoa. Whoa.

198
00:11:27,551 --> 00:11:30,315
Whoa. Hey, I think I'm gettin' it!

199
00:11:30,420 --> 00:11:32,320
Yes, that's great.

200
00:11:32,422 --> 00:11:35,755
Now let's just pull ourselves
out of this tailspin here.

201
00:11:35,859 --> 00:11:38,123
<i>[ Grunting ]</i>

202
00:11:38,228 --> 00:11:40,526
Whoo. Oh, I'm sorry about that.

203
00:11:40,630 --> 00:11:42,928
It's okay. That's what
the diapers are for.

204
00:11:46,002 --> 00:11:50,302
Now when the mama bird returns to feed
her babies we'll have a prize-winning picture.

205
00:11:50,407 --> 00:11:53,205
Lisa, people these days
don't wanna see a baby bird.

206
00:11:53,310 --> 00:11:55,369
They wanna see celebrities
at their worst.

207
00:11:55,478 --> 00:11:57,446
<i>[ Bell Dings ]</i>

208
00:11:58,615 --> 00:12:00,674
- Mmm. Mmm.
- Is that Rainier Wolfcastle?

209
00:12:00,784 --> 00:12:03,116
- Check out the gut.
- It's for a movie.

210
00:12:03,219 --> 00:12:06,655
I'm playing a fat secret agent.
Mmm. Mmm.

211
00:12:09,693 --> 00:12:12,161
Hey, Homer. Uh, no, no, no.
Don't sit there.

212
00:12:12,262 --> 00:12:14,162
Take this seat-
right next to the tap.

213
00:12:14,264 --> 00:12:16,494
But that's Barney's seat.

214
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:18,625
Are you trying to make me
the new Barney?

215
00:12:18,735 --> 00:12:21,431
Hey, every bar needs
a world-class drunk.

216
00:12:21,538 --> 00:12:24,564
Yeah, someone who makes our alcoholism
seems less raging.

217
00:12:24,674 --> 00:12:27,973
Well, forget it, guys.
I am not Barney.

218
00:12:28,078 --> 00:12:31,104
- [ Burps ]
- [ Laughing ]

219
00:12:31,214 --> 00:12:33,614
See, Homer?
It's not so bad.

220
00:12:33,717 --> 00:12:36,049
- Now dance, rummy.
- O-Okay.

221
00:12:36,152 --> 00:12:41,954
## [ Humming ]

222
00:12:43,693 --> 00:12:46,958
You danced for hours just
because they told you to?

223
00:12:47,063 --> 00:12:49,088
If I didn't, I'd lose their respect.

224
00:12:49,199 --> 00:12:51,224
<i>- [ Helicopter Whirring ]
- Huh?</i>

225
00:12:51,334 --> 00:12:54,167
<i>- [ Gasps ]
- Check it out, Homer. I'm flyin' this thing.</i>

226
00:12:54,270 --> 00:12:56,204
<i>Get it away from the house!</i>

227
00:12:56,306 --> 00:12:58,706
- Wanna go for a ride?
- Can I, Marge? Can I?

228
00:12:58,808 --> 00:13:00,605
<i>- Yes, go.Just go.
- [ Yowls ]</i>

229
00:13:03,013 --> 00:13:05,538
Oh, you missed some
big changes at Moe's.

230
00:13:05,649 --> 00:13:08,209
He hangs newspapers
over the urinals now.

231
00:13:08,318 --> 00:13:10,843
You can read the sports page
while you pee.

232
00:13:10,954 --> 00:13:13,047
Very la-di-da.

233
00:13:13,156 --> 00:13:15,124
I've made some big changes too.

234
00:13:15,225 --> 00:13:17,193
Can you believe
I'm flyin' this helicopter?

235
00:13:17,293 --> 00:13:19,193
- Power lines. Power lines!
- Whoops. Sorry.

236
00:13:19,295 --> 00:13:21,126
Whoa!

237
00:13:21,231 --> 00:13:25,861
- When I think about all the time
I wasted at Moe's-
- Wasted?

238
00:13:25,969 --> 00:13:27,994
What about our staring contests?

239
00:13:28,104 --> 00:13:31,039
And the way we always knew
what football coaches should've done.

240
00:13:31,141 --> 00:13:34,338
Remember the day we jumped that census guy
and stole his clicker?

241
00:13:34,444 --> 00:13:36,935
Those are all
priceless memories, Homer...

242
00:13:37,047 --> 00:13:39,572
but I don't wanna do
that stuff anymore.

243
00:13:39,683 --> 00:13:44,120
- Oh, so you're better than me. Is that it?
- I didn't say that.

244
00:13:44,220 --> 00:13:46,347
- Take me home.
- Oh, don't be that way, Homer.

245
00:13:46,456 --> 00:13:48,447
- I'll scream.
- Okay, okay.

246
00:13:53,630 --> 00:13:55,530
So how was your ride with Barney?

247
00:13:55,632 --> 00:13:58,032
I don't wanna talk about it.
[ Sobbing ]

248
00:13:58,134 --> 00:14:00,398
<i>- [ Door Closes ]
- [ Sobbing Continues ]</i>

249
00:14:00,503 --> 00:14:02,403
[ Mumbles ]

250
00:14:07,243 --> 00:14:09,973
[ Mumbling ]

251
00:14:10,080 --> 00:14:13,481
<i>[ Grunting ]
Stupid Barney. Thinks he's too good for me.</i>

252
00:14:13,583 --> 00:14:17,075
Cheer up, Homie.
You don't need friends to be happy.

253
00:14:17,187 --> 00:14:19,417
I haven't had a friend in years.

254
00:14:19,522 --> 00:14:21,717
But you got me.
Who have I got?

255
00:14:21,825 --> 00:14:25,192
Oh. Well, you still
have Lenny and Carl.

256
00:14:25,295 --> 00:14:27,627
Oh, Lenny and Carl suck!

257
00:14:27,731 --> 00:14:31,326
Please don't tell Lenny and Carl I said that,
'cause if I ever lost 'em as friends-

258
00:14:31,434 --> 00:14:34,892
If Barney's that important to you,
you've gotta work it out.

259
00:14:35,004 --> 00:14:40,135
Old friends stick together, like O.J. and A.C.,
or the Falcon and the Snowman.

260
00:14:40,243 --> 00:14:42,177
Oh, why can't I have a nickname?

261
00:14:44,414 --> 00:14:46,143
<i>[ Groans ]</i>

262
00:14:46,249 --> 00:14:48,945
<i>- [ Whining, Panting ]
- [ Lisa ] Okay, that's it.</i>

263
00:14:50,053 --> 00:14:52,851
Looks good.
Oh, Bart...

264
00:14:52,956 --> 00:14:54,981
the bulldog didn't ante.

265
00:14:56,292 --> 00:14:58,760
Okay, on three. One, two-

266
00:14:58,862 --> 00:15:02,263
Perfect. Phone book cover,
here I come. Ha-ha!

267
00:15:02,365 --> 00:15:04,458
Hey! No fair!

268
00:15:04,567 --> 00:15:06,933
Oh, we'll never get a good picture.

269
00:15:07,036 --> 00:15:09,197
Hey, why don't we dump
spaghetti on Maggie's head?

270
00:15:09,305 --> 00:15:11,865
- That picture's a cliché.
- Picture?

271
00:15:15,645 --> 00:15:19,513
Hey, Apu, you got any of those potato chips
that give you diarrhea?

272
00:15:19,616 --> 00:15:21,982
I need to do a little
spring cleaning.

273
00:15:22,085 --> 00:15:24,610
They're in the safety cabinet.
I'll get the key.

274
00:15:24,721 --> 00:15:27,155
<i>[ Bell Dings ]</i>

275
00:15:27,257 --> 00:15:30,385
- Oh, hello, Homer.
- Barney.

276
00:15:30,493 --> 00:15:32,484
- Beer, huh?
- That's right.

277
00:15:32,595 --> 00:15:34,495
- Enjoy.
- That I will.

278
00:15:34,597 --> 00:15:36,497
- Then we agree.
- You keep thinking that.

279
00:15:36,599 --> 00:15:37,623
- I will.
- Me too.

280
00:15:37,734 --> 00:15:39,634
<i>- Good day then.
- Good day then is right.</i>

281
00:15:39,736 --> 00:15:41,067
- Ta.
- Ta-ta.

282
00:15:41,171 --> 00:15:44,038
<i>- [ Bell Dings ]
- Hey, you did not pay for that beer!</i>

283
00:15:44,140 --> 00:15:45,767
[ Yelps ]

284
00:15:45,875 --> 00:15:49,402
<i>[ Birds Twittering ]</i>

285
00:15:49,512 --> 00:15:52,743
Boy, you can see everything
from Mount Springfield-

286
00:15:52,849 --> 00:15:55,977
<i>- The Squidport, the old monorail-
- [ Bart ] The Rlay-Doh factory.</i>

287
00:15:59,222 --> 00:16:01,588
<i>- [ Buzzer Buzzes ]
- Crescent moon! Crescent moon!</i>

288
00:16:04,394 --> 00:16:06,760
Come on, Springfield.
Sparkle for me, baby.

289
00:16:06,863 --> 00:16:10,128
That's it. Heads up!

290
00:16:10,233 --> 00:16:13,031
Ow! Bart, that's hot.

291
00:16:13,136 --> 00:16:15,104
I said heads up.

292
00:16:21,845 --> 00:16:27,545
Lenny, Carl, I know a lot of people bad-mouth you
and focus on how you suck, but not me.

293
00:16:27,650 --> 00:16:29,550
To me, you're true-blue.

294
00:16:29,652 --> 00:16:32,678
<i>- Aw, thanks, big guy.
- Now dance, rummy.</i>

295
00:16:32,789 --> 00:16:37,317
- Okay. ## [ Humming Off-key ]
- Hiya, Moe.

296
00:16:37,427 --> 00:16:41,796
Well, if it isn't little Miss
''I'm not wasting my life anymore''...

297
00:16:41,898 --> 00:16:43,798
which he is.

298
00:16:43,900 --> 00:16:48,860
Moe, I've come here to make amends for
my disgraceful behavior over the last 20 years.

299
00:16:48,972 --> 00:16:51,440
- Oh, that's okay, Barn.
- No, it's not okay.

300
00:16:51,541 --> 00:16:54,442
I broke barstools,
befouled your broom closet...

301
00:16:54,544 --> 00:16:58,480
and made sweet love to your pool table,
which I then befouled.

302
00:16:58,581 --> 00:17:01,482
Well, that would explain
the drop-off in play.

303
00:17:01,584 --> 00:17:03,677
This is a Channel 6 News bulletin.

304
00:17:03,786 --> 00:17:06,414
Fire has broken out
on Mount Springfield...

305
00:17:06,522 --> 00:17:08,888
trapping two youngsters
and their camera.

306
00:17:08,992 --> 00:17:11,017
Oh, no. That's Bart and Lisa!

307
00:17:11,127 --> 00:17:14,358
Unfortunately, fire trucks are unavailable
to fight the blaze...

308
00:17:14,464 --> 00:17:18,332
<i>as they're all being used to film the new
Burt Reynolds movie, Fireball and Mudflap.</i>

309
00:17:18,434 --> 00:17:20,334
I caught up with Burt on the set.

310
00:17:20,436 --> 00:17:23,963
<i>So, Burt, tell us a little about
Fireball and Mudflap.</i>

311
00:17:24,073 --> 00:17:26,007
Well, I playJerry ''Fireball'' Mudflap...

312
00:17:26,109 --> 00:17:29,567
a feisty Supreme Court justice,
who's searching for his birth mother...

313
00:17:29,679 --> 00:17:32,079
while competing in
a cross-country fire truck race.

314
00:17:32,181 --> 00:17:34,581
It's garbage.

315
00:17:36,486 --> 00:17:39,080
Barney, you gotta fly us
up there and save my kids.

316
00:17:39,188 --> 00:17:41,656
I can't.
I've never flown solo.

317
00:17:41,758 --> 00:17:45,421
Barney, the call is from heroism.

318
00:17:45,528 --> 00:17:47,621
Will you accept the charges?

319
00:17:47,730 --> 00:17:50,528
<i>[ Groaning ]</i>

320
00:17:55,138 --> 00:17:57,106
Where are you going?
The fire's that way.

321
00:17:57,206 --> 00:18:00,505
I know. I know. I haven't
learned right turns yet.

322
00:18:00,610 --> 00:18:01,838
- Aaah! Look out!
- [ Shouts ]

323
00:18:01,945 --> 00:18:05,813
<i>- [ Shouts ]
- Aaah!</i>

324
00:18:06,849 --> 00:18:08,749
<i>- [ Grunts ]
- [ Horns Honking ]</i>

325
00:18:08,851 --> 00:18:10,546
[ Tires Screeching ]

326
00:18:10,653 --> 00:18:13,554
I can't do this.
My nerves are shot.

327
00:18:13,656 --> 00:18:16,284
<i>- [ Grunting ]
- [ Horn Honking ]</i>

328
00:18:16,392 --> 00:18:18,519
[ Tires Squealing ]

329
00:18:20,863 --> 00:18:24,355
- Beer! That's what I need!
- Barney, no! Don't!

330
00:18:24,467 --> 00:18:27,095
<i>Yes! I need it.
[ Groans ]</i>

331
00:18:27,203 --> 00:18:30,604
<i>No! You've gotta be sober for this.
Give me that.</i>

332
00:18:30,707 --> 00:18:33,198
<i>[ Gulping ]
Ew, it's warm.</i>

333
00:18:34,510 --> 00:18:37,001
- You can't drink 'em all.
- Oh, yes, I can.

334
00:18:37,113 --> 00:18:39,809
<i>- I'll-
- [ Grunting ] Give me that.</i>

335
00:18:45,521 --> 00:18:48,615
I won't let you give up now
when you worked so hard-

336
00:18:48,725 --> 00:18:52,388
[ Slurring ]
to be the greatest pal in the world.

337
00:18:52,495 --> 00:18:54,690
I love you.

338
00:18:54,797 --> 00:18:57,391
Let's not lose touch
after graduation.

339
00:18:57,500 --> 00:19:00,025
[ Snoring ]

340
00:19:01,070 --> 00:19:03,038
You brave man.

341
00:19:03,139 --> 00:19:05,334
You took six silver bullets for me.

342
00:19:05,441 --> 00:19:09,070
Stay away from my wife.
[ Mumbles ]

343
00:19:10,580 --> 00:19:12,707
Looks like it's up to me.

344
00:19:22,959 --> 00:19:25,223
- [ Sighs ]
- We should be safe up here.

345
00:19:25,328 --> 00:19:27,228
I'm pretty sure fires
can't climb trees.

346
00:19:27,330 --> 00:19:29,230
- Ow!
- Dad!

347
00:19:29,332 --> 00:19:33,428
- Hi, kids! [ Laughs ]
- Hang on. I'll throw you a ladder.

348
00:19:36,039 --> 00:19:38,030
[ Shouting ]

349
00:19:38,141 --> 00:19:41,406
<i>- [ Grunting ]
- [ Screams ] Get off!. Get off!.</i>

350
00:19:43,513 --> 00:19:45,481
<i>[ Groans ]</i>

351
00:19:45,581 --> 00:19:47,674
<i>[ Grunting ]</i>

352
00:19:49,152 --> 00:19:51,052
- Dad, help!
- Help!

353
00:19:51,154 --> 00:19:53,054
All right, I'm comin'.

354
00:19:53,156 --> 00:19:55,522
[ Both Shouting ]

355
00:19:55,625 --> 00:19:59,152
Let me know if you're gonna
do that again, Homer.

356
00:20:06,803 --> 00:20:08,771
[ Shouting ]

357
00:20:12,475 --> 00:20:16,434
- You did it, Dad!
- You can't prove I did it.

358
00:20:16,546 --> 00:20:19,344
No! You saved our lives.

359
00:20:19,449 --> 00:20:22,577
I could do a lot of things
if I had some money.

360
00:20:22,685 --> 00:20:25,176
<i>- What?
- Now there's a picture.</i>

361
00:20:26,355 --> 00:20:28,323
<i>[ Shutter Clicks ]</i>

362
00:20:31,994 --> 00:20:34,690
Kids! The new phone books are here...

363
00:20:34,797 --> 00:20:37,698
and your picture's on the cover!

364
00:20:37,800 --> 00:20:39,825
- All right!
- Whoa! Cool! Let me see!

365
00:20:39,936 --> 00:20:42,336
[ Screaming ]

366
00:20:42,438 --> 00:20:46,704
Isn't it adorable? I guess some
baby pictures were on that old roll of film.

367
00:20:46,809 --> 00:20:49,676
Oh, we'll be the laughingstock
of the whole town.

368
00:20:49,779 --> 00:20:52,009
Well, at least we won the bike.

369
00:20:52,115 --> 00:20:57,052
Actually, I took the picture,
so I gave my prize to the orphanage.

370
00:20:57,153 --> 00:20:58,347
- What?
- How could you?

371
00:20:58,454 --> 00:21:02,322
Just kidding.
I would never do that.

372
00:21:02,425 --> 00:21:04,518
<i>[ Gasping ]</i>

373
00:21:07,263 --> 00:21:11,165
- Well, I'm glad we're friends again.
- Yeah.

374
00:21:11,267 --> 00:21:15,135
- So what do you call this stuff?
- A double tall mocha latte.

375
00:21:16,272 --> 00:21:18,172
It's not bad.

376
00:21:18,274 --> 00:21:20,902
<i>Well, it ain't beer.</i>

377
00:21:21,010 --> 00:21:23,638
But at least I got
that monkey off my back.

378
00:21:23,746 --> 00:21:25,646
<i>[ Gulping ]
Ah.</i>

379
00:21:25,748 --> 00:21:27,648
<i>[ Gulping ]
Oh.</i>

380
00:21:27,750 --> 00:21:30,412
<i>[ Gulping ] Oh.
[ Burps ]</i>

381
00:21:30,520 --> 00:21:33,887
<i>Ha, ha. Nobody gets away from Moe.</i>

382
00:21:33,990 --> 00:21:35,787
Nobody.

383
00:21:35,892 --> 00:21:38,861
[ Steam Hissing ]

384
00:21:40,396 --> 00:21:42,591
<i>[ Laughing ]</i>

385
00:21:42,698 --> 00:21:44,598
<i>[ Coughing ]
Oh.</i>

386
00:21:44,700 --> 00:21:46,600
<i>[ Laughs, Coughs ]
Oh.</i>

387
00:22:25,708 --> 00:22:27,676
- [ Murmuring ]
- Shh!



